    <h3>What is Gender Based Violence?</h3>

    <p>
        Gender Based Violence refers to harmful actions that are directed at an individual based on their
        gender or sex, often disproportionately affecting women and girls. GBV includes physical, sexual,
        emotional or financial abuse and it's a widespread global issue that needs attention and needs prevention methods.
    </p>

    <p>
        Please note that if you have recently suffered an assault, please go to the nearest Police Station or <a>Book a physical appointment</a>
